Job Title: Senior Business Analyst - Target Operating Model
Ad Text:
Sydney

Drive enterprise transformation through business architecture
Collaborate with solution architects and delivery teams
Flexible hybrid working with career development opportunities

 

Shape the future of our operating model and enable strategic transformation. Join a team where your expertise in business architecture creates lasting impact.

 

About the Role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you’ll contribute to designing and implementing our Target Operating Model (TOM) and business architecture. You’ll work closely with solution architects and transformation teams to deliver scalable, customer-focused solutions that align with strategic objectives.

You will join our large Analysis Chapter that supports a variety of medium to large scale programs across the Suncorp Group. The Chapter consists of around 290 like-minded analysts, where ideas and best practice are shared via masterclasses and knowledge sharing.

What You’ll Do

Lead analysis for Target Operating Model design, ensuring alignment with enterprise strategy and transformation goals.
Document current and future state processes, identifying opportunities for optimisation and improved customer outcomes.
Collaborate with solution architects and delivery teams to validate requirements and ensure technical feasibility.
Facilitate workshops and stakeholder discussions to gather insights and drive consensus on business architecture.
Provide coaching and guidance to junior analysts, fostering capability uplift across the team.
Actively participate in agile delivery rhythms, including stand-ups, showcases, and planning sessions.

 

What You’ll Bring

Proven experience in Target Operating Model design and business architecture within complex organisations.
Strong background in business analysis with advanced knowledge of frameworks such as BABOK and Lean Six Sigma.
Ability to synthesise complex information into clear, actionable insights for stakeholders.
Experience collaborating with solution architects and transformation teams to deliver integrated solutions.
Proficiency with tools such as JIRA and Confluence for managing requirements and delivery.
Excellent facilitation, communication, and stakeholder engagement skills across all levels.

 

What You’ll Enjoy

Access our award-winning Shine platform – your central hub for exclusive perks, wellbeing support, career development, and recognition. Shine has been recognised for excellence in employee experience, making it easier than ever to access what matters most to you.

Hybrid working, flexible leave, 20 weeks paid parental leave, and up to 5 days paid flexible leave annually
Paid study support, career breaks, on-the-job learning, and a $1,000 referral bonus for eligible employees
Free wellbeing coaching, a dedicated Employee Council, and confidential EAP access
Discounts at 400+ retailers, insurance savings, gym memberships, and reduced super fees
Paid volunteer leave, donation matching, and unlimited emergency response leave
Performance-based bonuses and Suncorp shares for eligible employees
Diversity is celebrated through employee resource groups and inclusive policies for all families

Explore our full benefits: www.suncorpgroup.com.au/careers/benefits

At Suncorp we believe we are our best when our workforce is as diverse, talented and passionate as the communities in which we live and operate, and where our people feel included, valued and connected. We are passionate about inspiring our people by creating a diverse, accessible, and inclusive culture, offering flexible work, career development and internal mobility, and building connected relationships amongst our team members and with our customers.

If you require any support and adjustments to participate equitably in our recruitment process or in the workplace, we encourage you to contact melissa.turkington@suncorp.com.au for a confidential conversation. To apply for this opportunity, please submit your application directly via the link provided.

Ad Text:
Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst

Contract to 26/06/2026 with possible extension | Carseldine + WFH

We’re working with a leading Queensland government client to recruit an experienced Business Intelligence Analyst. In this role you will review existing processes and systems that collect and report on cameras and other road safety devices and work with stakeholders to determine requirements for the new platform.

Key Responsibilities:

Analysing and documenting data analytics, data warehousing, and reporting requirements with business and technical stakeholders.

Designing and documenting business processes related to use of analytics and reporting services, including self-service.

Conducting workshops and providing training (including the development of training material) and support to stakeholders and end users in how to use tools to visualise data and identify trends and patterns.

Building dashboards and reports using visualisation tools to support specific analytics and reporting needs.

Assist in organisational change management activities (for example conducting change impact assessments and developing transition plans) to embed new processes and build organisational capability related to analytics and reporting.

What we’re looking for:

Expertise in developing visualizations of data for analytics and canned reports using BI tools such as Tableau, Power BI, and/or Splunk.

Experience sourcing data from various types of on-premise and cloud database systems (Oracle, Postgres, AWS Analytics/Redshift, Azure Synapse, Snowflake).

Proven ability to conduct requirements gathering and design workshops, documenting functional requirements, user stories, and data conversion rules.

Experience working on modernisation and transformational projects, including Agile and hybrid delivery approaches, preferably in the public sector or large organizations.

Experience working with Geospatial data and cloud environments.

Proven ability to run training and knowledge transfer sessions in the use of BI tools and assess user needs related to change impacts.

Why apply through Lime Recruitment?

Enjoy two pay runs per week without contractor fees. As a Queensland-owned agency, we offer personalised service and are a Tier 1 supplier to the Queensland Government. Awarded Australia’s top-performing small agency in 2021 and 2022, with a finalist spot in 2023. Partner with Lime for genuine, experienced, friendly recruiters dedicated to securing the best opportunities for you. Apply now or contact Kate Gear on  0477 624 569 or kate@limejobs.com.au to find out more!

About EnergyAustralia

Energy is changing and the entire system is being remade, harnessing the sun and wind. At EnergyAustralia, our strategy is to lead and accelerate the clean energy transformation whilst making this transition to a clean energy future simple for all our customers.

The Team

The Trading Operations team within the Trading & Transition business unit is responsible for managing, enhancing, and extending EnergyAustralia’s electricity and gas wholesale market analyses and modelling capabilities to ensure that planning, trading, strategy, and policy decisions are informed by an in depth understanding of and insight into market drivers and directions. 

About the role

Embedded within the Trading Operations team, you would be part of the cross-functional agile team driving delivery of key analytical initiatives that substantially increase the value from EA’s wholesale markets portfolio.

These initiatives could include focusing on:

Operational or portfolio optimisation, forecasting, decision analysis.
Driving the adoption of relevant advanced analytics technologies within Trading, such as machine learning, AI, distributed computing.
Enhancing our auto-bidder for Battery Energy Storage Systems (BESS) to achieve improved outcomes or new features.
Extending our optimised auto-bidding capability to pumped hydro and/or thermal assets.
Partnering with our Physical Markets trading team to search for optimisation opportunities such as how we best bid into a peaking electricity market.
Support EA’s Specialised Businesses area in delivering products that add value to both the customer and the wholesale market portfolio.

The role requires the intersection of deep and highly specialised commercial and market knowledge with substantial experience in the application of advanced analytics techniques in production settings. 

What are we ideally seeking?

Tertiary qualifications in a quantitative discipline – Mathematics, Engineering, Operations Research, Data Science
Postgraduate qualifications or Masters degree in relevant field is highly desirable.
Experience in a wholesale energy trading environment highly regarded.
Demonstrated experience in leading the delivery of production advanced analytics tools.
Expert ability to get to the essence of data considering the business context, and distil key problem features into a transparent, accurate and useful model.
Experience in the development of analytical software through hands on delivery of commercial grade systems
Highly developed and deep commercial understanding of the NEM and other Australian energy markets, including specialised trading instruments including derivative products and energy and FCAS spot markets.

How to Apply

If you’re ready to ‘light the way’ towards your next career move, click the 'Apply’ button.

For a copy of the PD, visit the EnergyAustralia Careers page. 

Applications close Thursday 4th December at 11.55pm.

Job Title: Head of Financial Planning and Analysis
Ad Text:
About the Organisation

Life Without Barriers is a leading social purpose, not for profit organisation of 8,000 employees working in more than 500 communities across Australia. We support children, young people and families, people with disability, older people and people with mental illness. We work with people who are homeless and refugees and asylum seekers.   

Make a real difference in the lives of vulnerable Australians with this unique opportunity to provide both corporate expertise and community support. With a focus on people, not profit, Life Without Barriers’ corporate services team partners with our direct support staff, clients, and their families to ensure we continue our mission to change lives for the better.  If a truly inclusive, collaborative, and fast-paced work environment sounds like your next career move, this is an opening not to be missed.

We want to employ people who reflect the diversity of our clients to ensure we can support each client's individual needs and wants. We encourage people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander background and people with disability to apply.

About the role

Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) you will lead the Group Financial Planning and Analysis team of circa 6 FTE that provides short, mid and long term financial planning, analysis, and insights that support effective decision-making across the business to ensure financial sustainability and resilience of a budget/revenue that exceeds $800M per annum.

You will be responsible for supporting the CFO and Executive Leadership Team by implementing and embedding group financial planning and analysis services to support the achievement of LWB’s Strategy. You will leverage technology and establish the data and reporting systems to drive transparency and ownership of financials, while providing business leaders with timely financial insight that supports data-driven decision-making.

This is a permanent full time opportunity located in either Sydney, Newcastle or Brisbane. We are committed to our employees having access to an office environment while enabling flexible work options.

Skills & experience

Tertiary level qualifications in business, commerce, management or relevant field.
Qualified and registered Chartered or Certified Practising Accountant.
Extensive experience in managing the FP&A function in a large and complex organisation.
Experience with best practice Enterprise Performance Management tools including requirements definition and implementation.
Experience managing a dispersed team, fostering effective, high-performance focused on achieving team and organisational goals.
Demonstrated experience designing, developing and implementing budgeting and rolling and long-range forecast models across a large organisation.
Demonstrated experience in managing competing priorities and to deliver high quality outcomes within agreed timeframes.
Working knowledge of relevant legislative and regulatory environment for areas of business responsibility.
Strong leadership skills, with the ability to build a shared understanding of, and commitment to the organisation’s Purpose and Values.
Ability to drive organisation-wide initiatives and strong organisational, planning and prioritising ability.
The ability to influence and work collaboratively with a range of stakeholders including peers, employees, partners, and suppliers to achieve financially responsible outcomes

Successful candidates will be required to clear probity checks including National Criminal History Record Check.

Benefits

Opportunity to work for one of Australia's largest social purpose organisations.
Excellent tax benefits & access to monthly rostered days off.
Work with skilled professionals to enhance the lives of the people we support.

How to Apply

Include your resume and cover letter in one document, click ‘Apply’ and follow the prompts. For any enquiries relating to the position contact Mikaella at recruitment@lwb.org.au. Candidates with disabilities who require adjustments to the recruitment process or the application form in an alternate format can contact Mikaella at recruitment@lwb.org.au . 

Applications close at midnight AEDT 3 December 2025.

This is where corporate finance makes impact, helping drive the projects shaping the nation's energy future.

Are you ready to make an impact in the renewable energy sector? We’re looking for a Commercial Analyst to deliver financial insights and strategic analysis for large-scale solar and BESS projects.


What you’ll do:

Build and refine complex financial models to assess project and investment economics and guide investment decisions

Update and maintain portfolio and asset valuation models

Deliver accurate forecasting, scenario analysis, and sensitivity analysis to guide key investment decisions.

Analyse market trends and investment opportunities in renewable energy.

What we’re looking for:

Bachelor’s degree in finance, Economics, or Commerce (Masters preferred).

3+ years’ experience in financial modelling, investment analysis and reporting. Preferably gained within or advising the renewable energy, electricity or oil and gas industries.

Advanced skills in Excel and other financial modelling tools.

Strong analytical, problem-solving, and critical-thinking mindset.

Ability to convey complex financial concepts to non-financial stakeholders.

Detail-oriented, self-motivated, and able to work independently and collaboratively in a fast- paced environment.

 

Why join us:

Drive sustainability: Work on projects that accelerate the global energy transition.

Career growth: Opportunities to develop in a fast-paced, innovative environment.

Collaborative culture: Join a team passionate about making a real-world impact.

Apply now and help shape the future of clean energy! Submit your CV and  a brief cover letter outlining your experience.

Applications close: 11:55pm, Friday 12th December.

Please note: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted. Must have work rights to work in Australia without sponsorship.

About Us

Globally, energy markets are in transition to a net zero future and the entities within these markets are transforming their underlying business models to ensure that they stay relevant, sustainable and profitable. As one of Australia’s largest energy providers, we are proud of our purpose to lead and accelerate the clean energy transformation for all. Our ability to deliver on this Purpose will be dependent on our people.

In the Customer Advanced Analytics team, we provide a unique understanding of customers and the market. We turn data into powerful insights that shape the future of energy. Our team delivers a deep understanding of customers using advanced analytics to design products and value propositions that are compliant, customer-friendly, and built for growth.

Success here means creating the perfect balance of volume and value helping Residential, Business, and C&I customers choose EnergyAustralia and stay with us. If you’re passionate about data-driven innovation and making a real impact, this is where you belong.

About the Role

This is an exciting opportunity to apply your technical expertise and commercial insight to shape smarter customer decisions. You’ll design and refine advanced models that optimise decision-making across our operations and frontline systems.

Your work will include building and supporting a detailed, bottom-up model of monthly gross margin per account—leveraging high-resolution consumption and generation data to calculate individualised wholesale prices and solar avoided costs. These insights will help us accurately assess segment and campaign profitability, driving better outcomes for customers and the business.

Design and manage qualitative and quantitative research projects including surveys, focus groups, interviews, and usability testing
Develop research methodologies that balance rigor with business timelines and constraints
Manage relationships with external research agencies and vendors
Support delivery of Voice of Customer programs including NPS tracking and customer feedback analysis
Synthesize customer feedback across multiple touchpoints to identify themes and trends
Drive engagement of the VoC program throughout the business and working with stakeholders to ensure actions are being taken
Analyse research data from multiple sources to extract meaningful patterns and actionable insights
Translate complex research findings into clear, compelling narratives for diverse stakeholders
Create presentations and reports that effectively communicate insights and recommendations
Partner with Product, Marketing, and Digital teams to understand research needs and consult on approaches

How can you support the Clean Energy Transition

Min 3-5 years of experience in market research, customer research, or insights roles with demonstrated ability to design and deliver research projects end-to-end
Strong understanding of qualitative and quantitative research methodologies including survey design, sampling approaches, and analytical techniques
Excellent analytical skills with the ability to identify patterns, draw meaningful conclusions, and translate findings into actionable recommendations
Outstanding communication and presentation skills, with the ability to tell compelling stories with data to both technical and non-technical audiences
Proficiency with research tools and platforms (survey tools such as Forsta; analysis software)
Strong project management skills with the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and deliver on time\

If you share our passion for a clean energy future for all and want to join us #Doing. Not just dreaming, then click the 'Apply’ button.

Why Us?

We’re committed to providing an inclusive culture so our people can bring their whole selves to work and have a sense of belonging. From our PRISM network that creates a positive culture for LGBTI employees to our Reconciliation Action Plan that has commitments to strengthen relationships with Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and organisations, it’s a workplace where everyone’s welcome.  We offer;

Employee discount on your electricity and gas, discounts on major brands and products
Annual Performance Bonus
20 weeks’ paid parental leave that’s completely gender-equal
Energise Program - flexible working that is team centric enabling all individuals to agree and succeed together
Excellent company culture, down-to-earth and friendly organisation - be authentic, bring your whole self to work!
2 paid recharge days
State-of-the-art Melbourne office, stunning views only 3-4 minute walk from Southern Cross station
Onsite Tech Bar

N.B Please be aware the position title is known internally as Research Specialist

Canberra ACT
Contract – Backfill (Up to 6 Months Maximum)
Federal Government

Are you:

A skilled Data Engineer experienced in data pipelines, data modelling, and analytics platforms?

Confident working with SQL, ETL/ELT processes, data warehousing, and cloud data environments?

Strong in Power BI, particularly in building semantic models, DAX measures, and high-quality datasets?

Comfortable stepping into an existing government project and providing immediate continuity and support?

If so, we welcome your application.

Role Overview

This is a short-term backfill role (maximum 6 months) supporting an established team within a major government program. Immediate start.

As a Data Engineer, you will ensure continuity of data operations by:

Maintaining and enhancing existing data pipelines and integration workflows

Supporting ongoing Power BI reporting, data modelling, and quality assurance

Ensuring that established data assets, dashboards, and reporting structures continue to operate reliably

Assisting the team with data preparation, transformation, and issue resolution

You will be expected to deliver immediate value, working within existing platforms, processes, and technical frameworks.

Key Responsibilities

Data Engineering & Integration

Maintain, troubleshoot, and improve ETL/ELT pipelines supporting operational and reporting needs

Work with SQL, Python, cloud-native ETL tools, and existing DevOps frameworks

Enhance and support data warehouses, data lakes, and curated datasets

Integrate data from multiple enterprise sources, APIs, and legacy systems

Power BI Data Modelling & Support

Maintain and update Power BI datasets, dataflows, and semantic models

Develop and refine DAX measures, hierarchies, and relationships

Ensure dashboards refresh reliably and data remains accurate

Support analysts and stakeholders using the existing reporting environment

Team Support & Collaboration

Provide continuity of service during a staff absence

Work closely with product teams, analysts, and developers to address data issues quickly

Translate business needs into technical tasks within the current architecture

Participate in Agile ceremonies and contribute to sprint deliverables

Governance, Compliance & DevOps

Ensure data handling aligns with APS security, privacy, and governance requirements

Use Azure DevOps for version control, backlog management, and job monitoring

Apply quality assurance measures to ensure data remains trustworthy and complete

 Eligibility Requirements

Demonstrated experience in data engineering within government or large enterprise environments

Proficiency in:

SQL (advanced querying and data manipulation)

Power BI (data modelling, DAX, dataset optimisation)

ETL/ELT and data integration

Experience with Azure, AWS, or other cloud analytics platforms

Experience using Azure DevOps or equivalent tooling

Minimum Baseline security clearance

Why This Role?

This is an ideal opportunity for someone who:

Enjoys stepping into an existing environment and ensuring continuity of data operations

Wants a 6-month engagement supporting a high-performing government analytics team

Prefers a role with clear expectations, established processes, and defined deliverables

Values modern cloud and analytics technologies without long-term transformation pressure

Ad Text:
Employment Type: full time continuing role, UNSW IT, Senior Integration Analyst
Starting salary $148012 plus generous super and leave loading
Location: Kensington campus in NSW (Hybrid Flexible Working)

About UNSW:

UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. We’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community; a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. It’s the reason we’re one of the top 50 universities in the world and a member of Australia’s prestigious Group of Eight. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

The Senior Integration Analyst is responsible for the core integration platform as well as for the development of services using the platform. This includes the implementation of new core integration requirements as well as supporting projects using the integration platform. The position will report to the Head of Integration and has no direct reports.

Specific accountabilities for this role include:

Lead hands-on development / configuration or coordinate the implementation with internal IT Teams and selected vendors. This includes delivery of central integration components as well as components to be integrated into business applications.
Enhance the UNSW IT standard integration platform based on Microsoft technology stack.
Analyse specified requirements and architectures to design appropriate objects and methods to implement specified functional and non-functional requirements.
Guide developers and coordinate with internal organisational units (e.g. Architecture, Service Management, Application owners) as well as suppliers during implementation.
Lead the collaborative creation and iteration of viable specifications and acceptance criteria in preparation for the deployment of information and communication systems.
Coordinate infrastructure or integration platform changes to integrate applications into the technology landscape
Design and implement Web Service interfaces, and implement integration logic (orchestration, transformation) in the Microsoft Azure Platform.
In collaboration with Architect’s review application software for compliance with integration standards and conformance with agreed architecture
Recommend/design structures and tools for systems which meet business needs and takes into account target environment, performance and security requirements and existing systems.
Translate logical designs into physical designs and produces detailed design documentation.
Specify and develop test scenarios to test those new/updated processes deliver improved ways of working for the end user at the same time as delivering efficiencies and planned business benefits.

We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join our growing team and help shape the future of our cloud-native data platform. Work with cross-functional teams (Architecture, Infrastructure, Security) to ensure alignment with enterprise standards.

Participate in all stages of the data engineering lifecycle: design, development, testing, deployment and documentation.

Other Duties

Shape and evolve the architecture of our cloud data platform, ensuring it scales with business growth.

Contribute to the development of best practices and reusable frameworks for data ingestion and transformation.

ABOUT YOU

Proven experience in cloud-based ETL/ELT development, ideally in Azure.

Strong proficiency in Python for data engineering tasks.

Hands-on experience with Databricks and Spark.

Solid understanding of data warehousing principles and best-practice modelling.

Ability to work independently and manage complexity in a dynamic environment.

Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Other

Experience with CI/CD pipelines.

Exposure to other cloud platforms and a range of data ingestion tools.

Familiarity with data governance and security frameworks.

Education & Experience

Essential

Minimum 5 years of experience in data engineering or related fields.

Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Data Engineering or a related discipline.

Other

Experience with Databricks, Python, Azure Data Factory, and SQL Server is highly desirable.

Experience ingesting real-time data (telemetry data) would be a bonus.

Job Title: Head of Financial Planning and Analysis
Ad Text:
About the Organisation

Life Without Barriers is a leading social purpose, not for profit organisation of 8,000 employees working in more than 500 communities across Australia. We support children, young people and families, people with disability, older people and people with mental illness. We work with people who are homeless and refugees and asylum seekers.   

Make a real difference in the lives of vulnerable Australians with this unique opportunity to provide both corporate expertise and community support. With a focus on people, not profit, Life Without Barriers’ corporate services team partners with our direct support staff, clients, and their families to ensure we continue our mission to change lives for the better.  If a truly inclusive, collaborative, and fast-paced work environment sounds like your next career move, this is an opening not to be missed.

We want to employ people who reflect the diversity of our clients to ensure we can support each client's individual needs and wants. We encourage people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander background and people with disability to apply.

About the role

Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) you will lead the Group Financial Planning and Analysis team of circa 6 FTE that provides short, mid and long term financial planning, analysis, and insights that support effective decision-making across the business to ensure financial sustainability and resilience of a budget/revenue that exceeds $800M per annum.

You will be responsible for supporting the CFO and Executive Leadership Team by implementing and embedding group financial planning and analysis services to support the achievement of LWB’s Strategy. You will leverage technology and establish the data and reporting systems to drive transparency and ownership of financials, while providing business leaders with timely financial insight that supports data-driven decision-making.

This is a permanent full time opportunity located in either Sydney, Newcastle or Brisbane. We are committed to our employees having access to an office environment while enabling flexible work options.

Skills & experience

Tertiary level qualifications in business, commerce, management or relevant field.
Qualified and registered Chartered or Certified Practising Accountant.
Extensive experience in managing the FP&A function in a large and complex organisation.
Experience with best practice Enterprise Performance Management tools including requirements definition and implementation.
Experience managing a dispersed team, fostering effective, high-performance focused on achieving team and organisational goals.
Demonstrated experience designing, developing and implementing budgeting and rolling and long-range forecast models across a large organisation.
Demonstrated experience in managing competing priorities and to deliver high quality outcomes within agreed timeframes.
Working knowledge of relevant legislative and regulatory environment for areas of business responsibility.
Strong leadership skills, with the ability to build a shared understanding of, and commitment to the organisation’s Purpose and Values.
Ability to drive organisation-wide initiatives and strong organisational, planning and prioritising ability.
The ability to influence and work collaboratively with a range of stakeholders including peers, employees, partners, and suppliers to achieve financially responsible outcomes

Successful candidates will be required to clear probity checks including National Criminal History Record Check.

Benefits

Opportunity to work for one of Australia's largest social purpose organisations.
Excellent tax benefits & access to monthly rostered days off.
Work with skilled professionals to enhance the lives of the people we support.

How to Apply

Include your resume and cover letter in one document, click ‘Apply’ and follow the prompts. For any enquiries relating to the position contact Mikaella at recruitment@lwb.org.au. Candidates with disabilities who require adjustments to the recruitment process or the application form in an alternate format can contact Mikaella at recruitment@lwb.org.au . 

Applications close at midnight AEDT 3 December 2025.

This is where corporate finance makes impact, helping drive the projects shaping the nation's energy future.

Are you ready to make an impact in the renewable energy sector? We’re looking for a Commercial Analyst to deliver financial insights and strategic analysis for large-scale solar and BESS projects.


What you’ll do:

Build and refine complex financial models to assess project and investment economics and guide investment decisions

Update and maintain portfolio and asset valuation models

Deliver accurate forecasting, scenario analysis, and sensitivity analysis to guide key investment decisions.

Analyse market trends and investment opportunities in renewable energy.

What we’re looking for:

Bachelor’s degree in finance, Economics, or Commerce (Masters preferred).

3+ years’ experience in financial modelling, investment analysis and reporting. Preferably gained within or advising the renewable energy, electricity or oil and gas industries.

Advanced skills in Excel and other financial modelling tools.

Strong analytical, problem-solving, and critical-thinking mindset.

Ability to convey complex financial concepts to non-financial stakeholders.

Detail-oriented, self-motivated, and able to work independently and collaboratively in a fast- paced environment.

 

Why join us:

Drive sustainability: Work on projects that accelerate the global energy transition.

Career growth: Opportunities to develop in a fast-paced, innovative environment.

Collaborative culture: Join a team passionate about making a real-world impact.

Apply now and help shape the future of clean energy! Submit your CV and  a brief cover letter outlining your experience.

Applications close: 11:55pm, Friday 12th December.

Please note: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted. Must have work rights to work in Australia without sponsorship.

About Us

Globally, energy markets are in transition to a net zero future and the entities within these markets are transforming their underlying business models to ensure that they stay relevant, sustainable and profitable. As one of Australia’s largest energy providers, we are proud of our purpose to lead and accelerate the clean energy transformation for all. Our ability to deliver on this Purpose will be dependent on our people.

In the Customer Advanced Analytics team, we provide a unique understanding of customers and the market. We turn data into powerful insights that shape the future of energy. Our team delivers a deep understanding of customers using advanced analytics to design products and value propositions that are compliant, customer-friendly, and built for growth.

Success here means creating the perfect balance of volume and value helping Residential, Business, and C&I customers choose EnergyAustralia and stay with us. If you’re passionate about data-driven innovation and making a real impact, this is where you belong.

About the Role

This is an exciting opportunity to apply your technical expertise and commercial insight to shape smarter customer decisions. You’ll design and refine advanced models that optimise decision-making across our operations and frontline systems.

Your work will include building and supporting a detailed, bottom-up model of monthly gross margin per account—leveraging high-resolution consumption and generation data to calculate individualised wholesale prices and solar avoided costs. These insights will help us accurately assess segment and campaign profitability, driving better outcomes for customers and the business.

Design and manage qualitative and quantitative research projects including surveys, focus groups, interviews, and usability testing
Develop research methodologies that balance rigor with business timelines and constraints
Manage relationships with external research agencies and vendors
Support delivery of Voice of Customer programs including NPS tracking and customer feedback analysis
Synthesize customer feedback across multiple touchpoints to identify themes and trends
Drive engagement of the VoC program throughout the business and working with stakeholders to ensure actions are being taken
Analyse research data from multiple sources to extract meaningful patterns and actionable insights
Translate complex research findings into clear, compelling narratives for diverse stakeholders
Create presentations and reports that effectively communicate insights and recommendations
Partner with Product, Marketing, and Digital teams to understand research needs and consult on approaches

How can you support the Clean Energy Transition

Min 3-5 years of experience in market research, customer research, or insights roles with demonstrated ability to design and deliver research projects end-to-end
Strong understanding of qualitative and quantitative research methodologies including survey design, sampling approaches, and analytical techniques
Excellent analytical skills with the ability to identify patterns, draw meaningful conclusions, and translate findings into actionable recommendations
Outstanding communication and presentation skills, with the ability to tell compelling stories with data to both technical and non-technical audiences
Proficiency with research tools and platforms (survey tools such as Forsta; analysis software)
Strong project management skills with the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and deliver on time\

If you share our passion for a clean energy future for all and want to join us #Doing. Not just dreaming, then click the 'Apply’ button.

Why Us?

We’re committed to providing an inclusive culture so our people can bring their whole selves to work and have a sense of belonging. From our PRISM network that creates a positive culture for LGBTI employees to our Reconciliation Action Plan that has commitments to strengthen relationships with Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and organisations, it’s a workplace where everyone’s welcome.  We offer;

Employee discount on your electricity and gas, discounts on major brands and products
Annual Performance Bonus
20 weeks’ paid parental leave that’s completely gender-equal
Energise Program - flexible working that is team centric enabling all individuals to agree and succeed together
Excellent company culture, down-to-earth and friendly organisation - be authentic, bring your whole self to work!

A skilled Data Engineer experienced in data pipelines, data modelling, and analytics platforms?

Strong in Power BI, particularly in building semantic models, DAX measures, and high-quality datasets?

Comfortable stepping into an existing government project and providing immediate continuity and support?

Role Overview

This is a short-term backfill role (maximum 6 months) supporting an established team within a major government program. Immediate start.

As a Data Engineer, you will ensure continuity of data operations by:

Maintaining and enhancing existing data pipelines and integration workflows

Supporting ongoing Power BI reporting, data modelling, and quality assurance

Ensuring that established data assets, dashboards, and reporting structures continue to operate reliably

Assisting the team with data preparation, transformation, and issue resolution

You will be expected to deliver immediate value, working within existing platforms, processes, and technical frameworks.

Key Responsibilities

Data Engineering & Integration

Maintain, troubleshoot, and improve ETL/ELT pipelines supporting operational and reporting needs

Work with SQL, Python, cloud-native ETL tools, and existing DevOps frameworks

Enhance and support data warehouses, data lakes, and curated datasets

Integrate data from multiple enterprise sources, APIs, and legacy systems

Power BI Data Modelling & Support

Maintain and update Power BI datasets, dataflows, and semantic models

Develop and refine DAX measures, hierarchies, and relationships

Ensure dashboards refresh reliably and data remains accurate

Support analysts and stakeholders using the existing reporting environment

Team Support & Collaboration

Provide continuity of service during a staff absence

Work closely with product teams, analysts, and developers to address data issues quickly

Translate business needs into technical tasks within the current architecture

Participate in Agile ceremonies and contribute to sprint deliverables

Governance, Compliance & DevOps

Ensure data handling aligns with APS security, privacy, and governance requirements

Use Azure DevOps for version control, backlog management, and job monitoring

Apply quality assurance measures to ensure data remains trustworthy and complete

 Eligibility Requirements

Demonstrated experience in data engineering within government or large enterprise environments

Proficiency in:

SQL (advanced querying and data manipulation)

Power BI (data modelling, DAX, dataset optimisation)

ETL/ELT and data integration

Experience with Azure, AWS, or other cloud analytics platforms

Experience using Azure DevOps or equivalent tooling

Minimum Baseline security clearance

Why This Role?

This is an ideal opportunity for someone who:

Enjoys stepping into an existing environment and ensuring continuity of data operations

Wants a 6-month engagement supporting a high-performing government analytics team

Prefers a role with clear expectations, established processes, and defined deliverables

Values modern cloud and analytics technologies without long-term transformation pressure

Ad Text:
Employment Type: full time continuing role, UNSW IT, Senior Integration Analyst
Starting salary $148012 plus generous super and leave loading
Location: Kensington campus in NSW (Hybrid Flexible Working)

About UNSW:

UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. We’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community; a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. It’s the reason we’re one of the top 50 universities in the world and a member of Australia’s prestigious Group of Eight. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

The Senior Integration Analyst is responsible for the core integration platform as well as for the development of services using the platform. This includes the implementation of new core integration requirements as well as supporting projects using the integration platform. The position will report to the Head of Integration and has no direct reports.

Specific accountabilities for this role include:

Lead hands-on development / configuration or coordinate the implementation with internal IT Teams and selected vendors. This includes delivery of central integration components as well as components to be integrated into business applications.
Enhance the UNSW IT standard integration platform based on Microsoft technology stack.

Are you a data science expert passionate about AI innovation and stakeholder influence? We’re seeking a Staff Data Scientist to drive cutting-edge AI advancements while working closely with executives and non-technical stakeholders to shape AI adoption and impact.
This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of technical excellence and business strategy, ensuring AI solutions deliver real value across the organisation.

About the Role
As a Lead or Principal Data Scientist, you will play a crucial role in developing and deploying machine learning models, optimising AI performance, and influencing key business decisions. Your expertise in NLP, LLMs, and MLOps will drive innovation, while your ability to communicate complex AI concepts to executives will ensure AI initiatives align with business objectives.
This is a high-visibility role where you’ll work across teams, bridging the gap between technical execution and business strategy—helping senior stakeholders understand the power of AI and how to apply it effectively.

Key Responsibilities
AI Strategy & Business Alignment – Work closely with executives and business leaders to integrate AI-driven solutions into company strategy.
Technical Leadership – Design, develop, and optimise machine learning models, with a focus on NLP and large-scale AI applications.
Executive Stakeholder Influence – Translate complex AI concepts into clear, actionable insights for non-technical leaders.
MLOps & AI Engineering – Implement best practices for model deployment, monitoring, and performance optimisation at scale.
Data-Driven Decision Making – Drive high-impact AI initiatives by leveraging advanced analytics on structured and unstructured data.
Research & Innovation – Stay ahead of AI trends, applying cutting-edge techniques to enhance business performance and operational efficiency.
What You’ll Bring
8+ years of experience (Staff Level) in data science, AI, and machine learning, with strong expertise in NLP and LLMs.
A track record of engaging with C-suite and senior business stakeholders, influencing AI strategy and execution.
Expert-level Python and SQL skills, with deep experience in building and deploying machine learning models at scale.
Hands-on experience with MLOps best practices, cloud-based AI solutions, and large-scale data processing.
A strategic mindset, with the ability to translate AI advancements into business impact.
Exceptional communication and influencing skills, able to simplify complex concepts for non-technical audiences.
What’s in It for You?
Work at the forefront of AI innovation, shaping strategy at a high-growth tech company.
Partner directly with executives and business leaders to drive enterprise-wide AI transformation.
Join a team that values curiosity, technical excellence, and real-world AI applications.
Hybrid work model (Sydney-based, 2-3 days in-office).
If you’re a highly experienced AI professional who can influence at an executive level while delivering cutting-edge AI solutions, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now!

Practical experience building RAG pipelines, integrating vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, FAISS), and deploying solutions through Databricks, SageMaker, or Vertex AI.

We’re looking for a talented and commercially minded Senior Pricing Analyst to join our growing team and play a key role in shaping pricing, portfolio performance and strategic growth across our home and motor insurance products. This role blends actuarial rigour, data analytics, and cross-functional collaboration to drive confident decisions that enhance customer value, support underwriting partnerships, and strengthen Honey’s product portfolio.

Who We Are

We're shaking up the home insurance industry! As a disruptor in the insurance space, we combine smart technology with exceptional service to create home insurance that's simpler, faster, and more customer-friendly. Our innovative approach includes smart sensors that help prevent incidents before they happen, a streamlined digital experience, and genuine human support when customers need it most.

About The Role

We’re seeking a Senior Pricing Analyst with strong actuarial capability, sharp commercial thinking, and a passion for data-driven decision-making. You’ll build and maintain pricing models, analyse portfolio performance, develop predictive models, and support strategic initiatives across product development, partnerships, and regulatory matters. You’ll work closely with teams across Product, Engineering, Finance and Operations, translating complex insights into clear and actionable recommendations.

Key Responsibilities

Pricing and portfolio analysis

Build and maintain pricing models across home, and motor insurance products
Analyse loss ratios, claim rates, and customer behaviour across segments to inform pricing decisions
Support pricing negotiations with underwriting partners by supporting actuarial analysis and business cases

Data analytics and reporting

Deliver regular reporting on portfolio performance, claims trends, and customer metrics across all product lines
Conduct deep-dive analyses on emerging risks, customer cohorts, and product performance
Develop predictive models to identify risk factors and optimise customer interventions
Create dashboards and visualisations to communicate insights to stakeholders

Strategic projects

Support product development and market entry decisions with actuarial analysis
Evaluate new partnership opportunities and distribution channels
Contribute to business cases for technology investments and product enhancements
Collaborate on regulatory and compliance matters requiring actuarial input

Stakeholder engagement

Translate complex actuarial and data concepts into actionable recommendations for non-technical audiences
Build relationships across product, engineering, operations, and finance teams

What You'll Bring

Must haves

Associate (AIAA) or near-Associate level (Part II complete) with the Actuaries Institute
3-5 years of experience in general insurance (ideally across multiple product lines such as home, motor or pet)
Strong understanding of actuarial principles, loss reserving, and risk assessment
Advanced SQL for data extraction and transformation
Python or R for statistical analysis and modelling (pandas, scikit-learn, statsmodels)
Experience with data visualisation tools (Tableau, Looker, or similar)
Comfortable working with cloud data platforms
Understanding of modern data infrastructure and version control

What sets you apart

Ability to balance actuarial rigour with commercial pragmatism
Curiosity, comfort with ambiguity and able to work autonomously
Strong communication skills - you can explain technical concepts to diverse audiences
Detail-oriented but don't lose sight of the bigger picture
Interest in insurtech and how technology is reshaping insurance

Why You'll Love Honey

Competitive salary package with performance-based incentives
Opportunity to shape and lead a critical function in a high-growth company
Enviable company culture of innovation, collaboration and high performance
Hybrid work model blending office collaboration with remote flexibility
Monthly team lunches, celebrations, social events & initiatives

Our Hive Culture

At Honey, we do things differently. You'll notice this from your first interaction with our team through to your first day with us. We challenge expectations, seek better ways of working, and value innovation at every turn.

We're exceptional at what we do, and every team member brings unique talent to our hive. As an equal opportunity employer, we're committed to diversity and inclusion, it's in our DNA, not just something we talk about.
